      <solution id="sol-00003">
      <para id="para-00031">Is there a winner based on the first round? Why or why not?</para>
      <para id="para-00032">A majority of 48 total votes is required to win. Begin by finding 50 percent of 48, which is calculated asfollows: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><mrow><mn>0.50</mn><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>48</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn></mrow></math>. A majority is 25 or more. No candidate has a majority, so there is no winner based on the first round.</para>
      </solution>
