      <para id="para-00043">Repeat Step 2 — Count the number votes for each restaurant in the first-round election. Since we are using a list of preferences, we need to count the number of 1s received by each restaurant.</para>
      <para id="para-00044">Results of Round 2:</para>
      <list bullet-style="bulleted" id="list-00005">
      <item>Rainbow China — 2 votes</item>
      <item>Dough Boys — 2 votes</item>
      <item>Caribbean Flavor — 1 vote</item>
      </list>
      <para id="para-00045">No single restaurant has three votes. Eliminate Caribbean Flavor, which has the fewest votes.</para>
      <figure class="unnumbered" id="fig-00007">
      <table summary="" frame="all" id="table-00007">
      <title>Figure 11.8 Chionilis Family Restaurant Preferences Round 2 Elimination
      </title>
